sub usage {
    print <<'EOF';
Usage: lab8reg <command> [args...]

  FIFO Control:
    reset                           Soft reset FIFO
    status                          Show FIFO status (pkt_ready, full, empty, etc.)
    mode <0|1|2>                    Set FIFO mode (0=FIFO, 1=CPU, 2=GPU)
    drain                           Trigger packet drain

  BRAM access (auto-switches to CPU mode and back):
    fifo_read [start] [count]       Read BRAM words (default: 0, 8)
    fifo_write <addr> <hi> <lo>     Write 64-bit BRAM word (hex values, ctrl=0x00)
    bram_write_full <a> <c> <h> <l> Write BRAM word with explicit ctrl byte (all hex)

  Packet Routing:
    packet_echo [dst_port_hex]      Capture->inspect->rewrite header->drain (echo packet)
                                    dst_port: 01=MAC0, 04=MAC1, 10=MAC2, 40=MAC3
                                    If omitted, echoes back to source port

  CPU Control:
    cpu_status                      Show CPU status (halted, running, cpsr, etc.)
    cpu_reset                       Assert CPU reset (held in reset)
    cpu_start                       Start CPU (also sets mode=CPU)
    cpu_stop                        Stop CPU (held in reset)

  CPU Memory:
    cpu_load_imem <hex_file>        Load hex file into IMEM (resets CPU first)
    cpu_read_imem [start] [count]   Read IMEM words (default: 0, 16)
    cpu_read_dmem [start] [count]   Read DMEM words (default: 0, 8)
    cpu_write_dmem <addr> <hi> <lo> Write 64-bit DMEM word (hex values)

  CPU Debug:
    cpu_la_read [start] [count]     Read logic analyzer (default: 0, 16)
    cpu_test <hex_file>             Full CPU-FIFO test (load, write BRAM, run, verify)

  GPU Control:
    gpu_status                      Show GPU status (kernel_done, dma_busy, reset)
    gpu_reset                       Assert GPU reset (held in reset)
    gpu_start                       Release GPU reset (starts executing)
    gpu_stop                        Stop GPU (held in reset)

  GPU Memory:
    gpu_load_imem <hex_file>        Load hex file into GPU IMEM (resets GPU first)
    gpu_read_imem [start] [count]   Read GPU IMEM words (default: 0, 16)
    gpu_read_dmem [start] [count]   Read GPU DMEM words (default: 0, 8)
    gpu_write_dmem <addr> <hi> <lo> Write 64-bit GPU DMEM word (hex values)

  DMA:
    dma_fifo_to_gpu <f> <g> <len>   DMA FIFO BRAM[f..] -> GPU DMEM[g..] (len words)
    dma_gpu_to_fifo <g> <f> <len>   DMA GPU DMEM[g..] -> FIFO BRAM[f..] (len words)

  Integration Test:
    gpu_test <hex_file>             Full GPU-DMA test (packet -> DMA -> kernel -> DMA -> drain)

  NOTE: Base address is a placeholder (0x2001100). After first `make` on the
        VM, grep include/registers.v for LAB8_BLOCK_ADDR and update $BASE.
EOF
}

